obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

obo:ECO_0006052  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2103  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2,3; The authors use both a dom neg FLRT3 protein and a shRNA knockdown and observe a reduction in the number of exc. synapses. The membrane adhesion part of FLRT3 with LPHN3 is shown directly by co-cultured LPHN3-GFP expressing neurons and FLRT3 expressing HEK cells that induces clustering of LPHN3.. Experimental description: from Supplemental Experimental Procedures;\n\"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from P0 Long-Evans rats (Charles\nRiver) and plated on poly-D-lysine (Millipore), and laminin (Invitrogen) coated\nchamber slides (Nalge Nunc International).\"\n\nOverexpressed protein: \"Full-length cDNAs encoding mouse Flrt1, Flrt2, Flrt3, and Lphn3 (accession numbers BC070403, BC096471, BC052043, and BC088989, respectively) and a partial Lphn1 cDNA (BC085138) were purchased from Thermo Scientific/Open Biosystems\"\n\n11/12/2017 Pim\n- Because the most important data is obtained with the overexpressed mouse protein, I use mouse as selected species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2103" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

